  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Manager[Central/Maincon/Construction]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure all M&amp;E works are executed on schedule, adhering strictly to relevant codes, standards, and safety regulations.</li>\n  <li>Liaise and coordinate closely with clients, consultants, authorities, and subcontractors to address and resolve M&amp;E-related issues, ensuring seamless project execution.</li>\n  <li>Lead and manage the site team—including M&amp;E engineers, structural engineers, and architectural coordinators—to deliver quality outcomes that meet consultant specifications and client expectations.</li>\n  <li>Attend site-level Coordination &amp; Communication Meetings (CCM) to address and resolve technical challenges effectively.</li>\n  <li>Ensure timely preparation and submission of M&amp;E shop drawings, material approvals, and method statements, aligned with the M&amp;E master schedule.</li>\n  <li>Supervise and guide M&amp;E personnel, supervisors, and subcontractors to ensure works are executed in compliance with approved plans and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Review and verify M&amp;E-related Variation Orders and report progress or arising issues to the HQ.</li>\n  <li>Participate in site inspections and quality checks, and troubleshoot technical issues in M&amp;E systems as they arise.</li>\n  <li>Study and analyze consultant specifications, technical drawings, and design intent to identify discrepancies. Issue RFIs or coordinate directly with consultants and clients for resolution.</li>\n  <li>Organize and lead monthly M&amp;E meetings, overseeing and coordinating all M&amp;E activities comprehensively.</li>\n  <li>Address and resolve M&amp;E issues that emerge during the Defects Liability Period (DLP).</li>\n  <li>Contribute to Design &amp; Build (D&amp;B) projects, collaborating closely with consultants and architects from inception to completion.</li>\n</ul>",
